          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-06-26 16:40:49.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2600 osd-zfs: batched object accounting",
        "message": "LU-2600 osd-zfs: batched object accounting\n\nusing dsl_sync_task_do_nowait() we can schedule the updates\nto be executed in a closing txg. this way object accounting\ncan be done in memory and then updated in ZAPs once per txg.\n\nunfortunately the patch doesn't work with debugging enebled\nin ZFS. that's because the internals (e.g. dbuf_dirty()) do\nexpect only the special objects can be modified at syncing.\nand the special objects are those which dnode# < 0, which is\nnot so yet for the objects storing accounting.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly envdefinitions=SLOW=yes,ENABLE_QUOTA=yes \\\nmdtfilesystemtype=zfs mdsfilesystemtype=zfs ostfilesystemtype=zfs\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I213c51e4c0a59ba3b32872a38f83647b0b59f1ab\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
